Greek Parliament Begins Voting on Property Tax Motion

-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 
2011-09-27T16:53:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/greek-parliament-begins-voting-on-property-tax-motion.html
Greek lawmakers began casting their
ballots in a vote to approve a new property tax to meet 2011
budget targets and qualify for a sixth loan installment. The
roll-call vote in parliament in  Athens  is being televised live
on state-run Vouli TV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eleni Chrepa in Athens at 
 echrepa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  